Pre-heat your #oven{} to 180 degrees. Cut your @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice it finely into half moon shapes. Peel and chop your @garlic cloves{2}. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and cut into slices about 1cm wide. Slice your @courgette{1} in half lengthways and then slice into half moon shapes about 1 1/2cm thick. Chop each of your @British chicken thighs{3} into four pieces.

Bring @water{350%ml} to the boil in a #pot{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} (in preparation for your rice).

Add @oil{1%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat and throw in your onion, cook for ~{5%minutes} before adding your garlic and cooking for a further ~{1%minute}. Add your chicken to the pan and fry it with the onion for ~{4%minutes}, stirring occasionally until slightly browned.

In the meantime, add your pepper and courgette to a #baking tray{} with @oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{ground} and put in the oven to cook for ~{20-25%minutes}, until slightly crispy.

While your veggies are roasting, add your @basmati rice{1} to your boiling water, put the lid on and cook for ~{10%minutes}, before taking off the heat and leaving to rest for another ~{10%minutes}.

> Don't peek under the lid for the whole 20 mins.

When the chicken has been browned, add your @flour{2%tbsp} and @mild paprika{1.5%tsp} to the pan and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add @water{350%ml} to the pan along with @chicken stock pot{1/2} and bring to a boil. Then reduce the heat, put your lid on your pan and cook for ~{7%minutes}. After 7 mins, drain and rinse your @butter beans{1%400g can}, add them to the pan and cook for a further ~{7%minutes} uncovered.

When the chicken has been cooking for 15 mins, add your @sour cream{1}, @soy sauce{1%tbsp} and @honey{1%tbsp} and stir. Simmer for ~{2%minutes} and then serve on your rice with your peppers on top. Enjoy!